The paper discusses the implementation of neural networks using memristive neuromorphic systems, which falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) in computer science. The focus is on the synaptic crossbars, which are a key component of neuromorphic systems, and the impact of nonidealities on the performance of neural networks. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), as well as Architecture (cs.AR) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed solution involves incorporating mathematical models of nonidealities in the backpropagation algorithm, which could also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
